                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d479">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/799a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-04-17T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1928—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>124. Department’s 354, October 1, 4 p.m.<note n="42" xml:id="d479fn42">
                        <ref target="frus1927v02#pg_417">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1927, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 417</ref>.</note> What is present
                    status of proposed surtax? It is intimated to the Department that objection of
                    Japan only is preventing collection.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
